            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "albedo_sweep_at_default_solar",
                    "description": "Reproduces Seinfeld & Pandis Page 102 Figure 4.4 (planetary equilibrium temperature vs albedo) cast for the TOA component: sweep R_p from 0 to 0.9 at the default S_0 = 1370 W/m² and F_L = 239.75 W/m². At R_p = 0 the planet absorbs maximum solar and F_net peaks at +102.75 W/m² (strong warming forcing); at R_p = 0.3 the planet is in radiative balance F_net = 0; above R_p = 0.3 the planet emits more than it absorbs and F_net goes negative (cooling). Two output curves: F_S (absorbed solar) linearly decreasing from 342.5 to 34.25; F_net (net flux) linearly decreasing from +102.75 to -205.5 — the same shape since F_net = F_S - F_L is just a vertical translation. Anchors the (1-R_p) linear-response character of F_S, the most numerically important sensitivity in this component.",
