                    "description": "Sweep the emitted longwave flux F_L across the canonical climate-forcing range of ±10 W/m² around the equilibrium F_L = 239.75 W/m². Covers the full physically-motivated range from a strong negative forcing (F_L = 230, akin to large aerosol cooling or a major volcanic eruption) through equilibrium (F_L = 239.75) to a strong positive-forcing-equivalent (F_L = 249.75, akin to a 2x CO₂ doubling). F_S is unchanged at 239.75 (independent of F_L); F_net traces a strictly-linear y = 239.75 - F_L from +9.75 to -10.0, crossing zero at F_L = 239.75. The IPCC AR6 doubled-CO₂ instantaneous forcing of +4-5 W/m² maps to the F_L ≈ 235 sub-range on this plot.",
